<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="869" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/412A.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Inform Clark negotiations in Europe promise successful results and
                            bankers expect to issue bonds as soon as formal authority for their
                            execution is received from Monrovia. Papers to be signed were mailed
                            here by Falkner June 15. Bankers have prepared form of provisional bonds
                            and will execute them without delay when authorizations requested have
                            been received.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>